    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-18T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-18T14:00:00-05:00" n="142"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72112A/1300</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_BTH1"
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Birch</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-18T15:00:00-04:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 18, 1918, 3 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>305. Your 384, June 4, 10 a.m. Facts reported indicate little likelihood of <hi
                        rend="italic">bona fide</hi> liquidation of enemy interests. Unless you
                    disapprove, will plan to issue list for Portugal. Names to be reviewed in
                    conference with British, French, and Italian representatives in London following
                    joint recommendation from Lisbon. Cable opinion.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
